Sex workers continue to call on the government to protect and support them during the nationwide lockdown. #eNCA talks to Nosipho Vidima, Human Rights Officer for the Sex Worker Education and Advocacy Taskforce. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Sex workers continue to call on government to protect and support them during the nationwide lockdown. “During the lockdown, it became even more apparent to us. Sex workers will call and says I'm going to the store to get essentials and I've just been harassed. Police officers have just violated me...” said Nosipho Vidima of the Human Rights Officer for the Sex Worker Education and Advocacy Taskforce (SWEAT). Vidima said most sex workers are struggling to put food on the table during the lockdown. READ: Sex workers hardest hit by SA lockdown: SWEAT “We also blaming government and saying that if only you had decriminalised year earlier on, you'd have workers filing along with every worker for UIF,” she said. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.